{"id":1566,"date":"2024-11-03T21:18:24","date_gmt":"2024-11-03T21:18:24","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/manning-law-firm.local\/?page_id=1566"},"modified":"2024-11-18T22:55:52","modified_gmt":"2024-11-18T22:55:52","slug":"antitrust","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/manning-law-firm.local\/antitrust\/","title":{"rendered":"Antitrust"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-container uagb-block-49d17bf2 alignfull uagb-is-root-container\"><div class=\"uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-info-box uagb-block-441dcefd uagb-infobox__content-wrap  uagb-infobox-icon-above-title uagb-infobox-image-valign-top wp-block-uagb-info-box--has-margin\"><div class=\"uagb-infobox-margin-wrapper\"><div class=\"uagb-ifb-content\"><div class=\"uagb-ifb-title-wrap\"><div class=\"uagb-ifb-separator\"><\/div><h1 class=\"uagb-ifb-title\">Antitrust<\/h1><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-container uagb-layout-flex uagb-block-beb3ac1d alignfull uagb-is-root-container\"><div class=\"uagb-container-inner-blocks-wrap\">\n<p>Antitrust litigation involves legal actions arising from alleged violations of antitrust laws, which are designed to ensure fair competition and protect consumers. Federal and state antitrust laws address a wide range of issues, including price-fixing, monopolization, unfair competition, and unfair practices in mergers and acquisitions. Such cases can involve businesses coordinating unfair agreements, like fixing prices, dividing markets, or engaging in group boycotts, all of which stifle competition and harm consumers. Both public agencies and private entities can pursue claims against businesses for alleged antitrust violations under these laws.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Key federal statutes governing antitrust matters include the Sherman Act, which prohibits unreasonable trade restraints and monopolization; the Clayton Act, which restricts mergers and acquisitions that may harm competition; and the Federal Trade Commission Act, which bans unfair methods of competition and deceptive practices. Violations under these statutes may result in government investigations, private lawsuits, or both. Many cases stem from mergers or acquisitions, where premerger filings may prompt scrutiny from the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) or the Department of Justice (DOJ). State attorneys general may also bring suits under state antitrust laws or join federal actions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Antitrust litigation can also involve international disputes where practices affect markets across national boundaries. Such cases might involve foreign businesses suing U.S. companies or vice versa, particularly in industries with global trade significance. Private plaintiffs and businesses often seek damages for antitrust violations through litigation or class actions. Given the complexity and high stakes of antitrust cases, businesses must seek legal guidance to prepare defenses, ensure compliance, or pursue claims when harmed by anticompetitive behavior.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-advanced-heading uagb-block-b15807b9\"><h5 class=\"uagb-heading-text\"><strong>Why choose Ms. Manning? <\/strong><\/h5><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-icon-list uagb-block-fd3733eb\"><div class=\"uagb-icon-list__wrap\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-icon-list-child uagb-block-4097867c\"><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__source-wrap\"><svg xmlns=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\"><path d=\"M64 448c-8.188 0-16.38-3.125-22.62-9.375c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25L178.8 256L41.38 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25s32.75-12.5 45.25 0l160 160c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.75 0 45.25l-160 160C80.38 444.9 72.19 448 64 448z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__label\"><strong>Expertise in Key Legal Issues:<\/strong> Skilled in handling price-fixing, group boycotts, bid rigging, monopolization, market division, and unfair competition cases.<\/span><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-icon-list-child uagb-block-9ba65363\"><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__source-wrap\"><svg xmlns=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\"><path d=\"M64 448c-8.188 0-16.38-3.125-22.62-9.375c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25L178.8 256L41.38 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25s32.75-12.5 45.25 0l160 160c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.75 0 45.25l-160 160C80.38 444.9 72.19 448 64 448z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__label\"><strong>In-Depth Knowledge of Federal Laws:<\/strong> Proficient in the Sherman Act, Clayton Act, and Federal Trade Commission Act.<\/span><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-icon-list-child uagb-block-c48f317b\"><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__source-wrap\"><svg xmlns=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\"><path d=\"M64 448c-8.188 0-16.38-3.125-22.62-9.375c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25L178.8 256L41.38 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25s32.75-12.5 45.25 0l160 160c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.75 0 45.25l-160 160C80.38 444.9 72.19 448 64 448z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__label\"><strong>Experience with Enforcement Bodies:<\/strong> Extensive experience dealing with investigations by the FTC, DOJ, and state attorneys general.<\/span><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-icon-list-child uagb-block-19228e2e\"><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__source-wrap\"><svg xmlns=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\"><path d=\"M64 448c-8.188 0-16.38-3.125-22.62-9.375c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25L178.8 256L41.38 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25s32.75-12.5 45.25 0l160 160c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.75 0 45.25l-160 160C80.38 444.9 72.19 448 64 448z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__label\"><strong>Representation in Private Actions:<\/strong> Capable of filing and defending lawsuits under federal and state antitrust laws for businesses and individuals.<\/span><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-icon-list-child uagb-block-c00e12d1\"><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__source-wrap\"><svg xmlns=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\"><path d=\"M64 448c-8.188 0-16.38-3.125-22.62-9.375c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25L178.8 256L41.38 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25s32.75-12.5 45.25 0l160 160c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.75 0 45.25l-160 160C80.38 444.9 72.19 448 64 448z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__label\"><strong>Global Perspective:<\/strong> Expertise in managing international antitrust disputes involving cross-border trade and global competition.<\/span><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-icon-list-child uagb-block-9ac73a76\"><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__source-wrap\"><svg xmlns=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\"><path d=\"M64 448c-8.188 0-16.38-3.125-22.62-9.375c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25L178.8 256L41.38 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25s32.75-12.5 45.25 0l160 160c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.75 0 45.25l-160 160C80.38 444.9 72.19 448 64 448z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__label\"><strong>Focus on Mergers &amp; Acquisitions:<\/strong> Proven ability to address antitrust concerns in mergers, including premerger filings and government scrutiny.<\/span><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-uagb-icon-list-child uagb-block-eb6cb49e\"><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__source-wrap\"><svg xmlns=\"https:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 256 512\"><path d=\"M64 448c-8.188 0-16.38-3.125-22.62-9.375c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25L178.8 256L41.38 118.6c-12.5-12.5-12.5-32.75 0-45.25s32.75-12.5 45.25 0l160 160c12.5 12.5 12.5 32.75 0 45.25l-160 160C80.38 444.9 72.19 448 64 448z\"><\/path><\/svg><\/span><span class=\"uagb-icon-list__label\"><strong>Comprehensive Resolution Strategies: <\/strong>Skilled in resolving cases through litigation, consent orders, arbitration, or mediation, tailored to clients&#8217; needs.<\/span><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Antitrust litigation involves legal actions 